    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-09T11:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-09T11:26:00-05:00" n="545"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/2–954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State, at Berlin</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d545fn1">Drafted by Acting Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_SGWB1">Walter Bedell Smith</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-09T11:26:00-05:00"
                            >February 9, 1954—11:26 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 33. Eyes only for the Secretary.
                    Yesterday before I read <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 54<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d545fn2">
                        <ref target="#d544">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> I talked to <persName corresp="#p_BH1">Bonnet</persName> at
                    his request about aid for Indochina.<note n="3" xml:id="d545fn3">No additional
                        record of the <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1">Smith</persName>–<persName
                            corresp="#p_BH1">Bonnet</persName> meeting of Feb. 8 has been found in
                        Department of State files.</note> I mentioned various additional ways that
                    we might assist i.e., psychological, <pb facs="1058" n="1026" xml:id="pg_1026"/>
                    covert activities, training, etc. and touched on the rather cool reception given
                        <persName corresp="#p_OLGJ1">O’Daniel</persName>. At the same time I
                    suggested desirability that <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Pleven</persName> and
                    General <persName corresp="#p_EGP1">Ely</persName> might return via Washington.
                    It seems to me this would have two advantages. In the first place the President
                    could get first hand report from <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Pleven</persName>
                    while U.S. Chiefs of Staff heard from <persName corresp="#p_EGP1"
                    >Ely</persName>. Then if <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Pleven</persName> seemed to
                    show signs of weakening President might stiffen him up.</p>
                <p>If you agree as to desirability you might make suggestion to <persName
                        corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> putting it on basis of expedited and
                    increased material assistance as result of this contact.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d545fn4">At 11: 59 a.m., President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                            >Eisenhower</persName> called Acting Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_SGWB1">Smith</persName> to discuss a variety of issues.
                        During the conversation, aspects of the Indochina question, including the
                        possibility of a <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Pleven</persName>–<persName
                            corresp="#p_EGP1">Ely</persName> visit to Washington, were discussed
                        inconclusively. (<persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library,
                            <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> papers, Whitman file,
                        “Telephone Conversations”)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
